---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Refunds & Cancellations — DOKU">
  <div class="narrow">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Read this before you claim</div>
      <h1 class="serif">Refunds &amp; Cancellations</h1>
      <p>Every object here exists once. That changes what a refund can reasonably mean.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prov-pull">"We do not offer refunds for changed taste. We do for misrepresentation."</div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Before payment completes</h2>
      <p>Holding an object in your cart doesn't charge you anything. Remove it any time before checkout — there's nothing to cancel, because nothing has been claimed yet.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>After a successful payment</h2>
      <p>A verified payment reserves the object under your name. Because each piece is singular — not one of a batch — we don't run the kind of open-ended "change of mind" return window a stocked retailer can offer. Once it's yours, it's yours.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>When we do refund</h2>
      <ul class="legal-list">
        <li>The object is materially different from how it was described or photographed.</li>
        <li>We're unable to fulfil the order — it's damaged before it ships, or lost in transit before it reaches you.</li>
        <li>A payment was charged twice, or in error.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:16px;">In any of these cases, we issue a full refund through Razorpay, back to the original payment method.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>How a refund is processed</h2>
      <p>Refunds go back to the card or method you paid with, through Razorpay. How quickly it reflects depends on your bank or card issuer — we can't set that timeline, only start it. Once a refund is issued, your order shows as <strong>Refunded</strong> in your account.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Cancelling before it ships</h2>
      <p>If you'd like to cancel after paying but before we've shipped, tell us — <a href="/inquire">Inquire</a>, with your order code. We'll review it and, where it applies, process a refund.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>How to request one</h2>
      <p>There's no automatic self-serve button for this — a person reads every request. Write to us through <a href="/inquire">Inquire</a> with your order code and what happened. We reply, and we don't leave you re-explaining it to someone new.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="fine-print">See also <a href="/shipping">Shipping</a> for what happens if something goes missing on the way to you, and <a href="/terms">Terms</a> for the fuller agreement this sits inside.</p>

    <div class="legal-updated">Last updated 17 July 2026</div>
  </div>
</Base>
